#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:0
#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:9
msgid "Installing NixOS on a Raspberry Pi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:0
msgid "Raspberry Pi, rpi, NixOS, installation, image, tutorial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:11
msgid ""
"This tutorial assumes you have a [Raspberry Pi 4 Model B with 4GB RAM]"
"(https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-4-model-b/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:13
msgid ""
"Before starting this tutorial, make sure you have [all the necessary "
"hardware](https://projects.raspberrypi.org/en/projects/raspberry-pi-setting-"
"up/1):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:16
msgid "HDMI cable/adapter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:17
msgid "8GB+ SD card."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:18
msgid "SD card reader (in case your machine doesn't have an SD slot)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:19
msgid "Power cable for your Raspberry Pi."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:20
msgid "USB keyboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:23
msgid ""
"This tutorial was written for the Raspberry Pi 4B. Using a previously "
"supported model like the 3B or 3B+ is possible with some modifications to "
"this tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:26
msgid "Booting NixOS live image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:29
msgid ""
"Booting from USB may require an EEPROM firmware upgrade. This tutorial boots "
"from an SD card to avoid such hiccups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:32
msgid ""
"To prepare the AArch64 image on another device with Nix, run the following "
"commands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:34
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell -p wget zstd\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ wget https://hydra.nixos.org/build/226381178/download/1/nixos-"
"sd-image-23.11pre500597.0fbe93c5a7c-aarch64-linux.img.zst\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ unzstd -d nixos-sd-image-23.11pre500597.0fbe93c5a7c-aarch64-"
"linux.img.zst\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ dmesg --follow\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:43
msgid ""
"You can download a recent image from [Hydra](https://hydra.nixos.org/job/"
"nixos/trunk-combined/nixos.sd_image.aarch64-linux), clicking on the latest "
"successful build (marked with a green checkmark), and copying the link to "
"the build product image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:48
msgid ""
"It may be more convenient to use a software like [Etcher](https://www.balena."
"io/etcher/) to flash the image to your SD card if you are on a system where "
"it's available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:51
msgid "Your terminal should be printing kernel messages as they come in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:53
msgid ""
"Plug in your SD card and your terminal should print what device it got "
"assigned, for example `/dev/sdX`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:55
msgid "Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>C</kbd> to stop `dmesg --follow`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:55
msgid "<kbd>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:55
msgid "</kbd>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:57
msgid ""
"Copy NixOS to your SD card by replacing `sdX` with the name of your device "
"in the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:59
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:~]$ sudo dd if=nixos-sd-image-23.11pre500597.0fbe93c5a7c-aarch64-"
"linux.img of=/dev/sdX bs=4096 conv=fsync status=progress\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:63
msgid ""
"Once that command exits, **move the SD card into your Raspberry Pi and power "
"it on**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:65
msgid "You should be greeted with a fresh shell!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:67
msgid ""
"In case the image doesn't boot, it's worth [updating the firmware](https://"
"www.raspberrypi.com/documentation/computers/raspberry-pi."
"html#bootloader_update_stable) and booting the image again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:69
msgid "Getting internet connection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:71
msgid "Run `sudo -i` to get a root shell for the rest of the tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:73
msgid ""
"At this point you'll need an internet connection. If you can use an ethernet "
"cable, plug it in and skip to the next section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:75
msgid ""
"If you're connecting to wifi, run `iwconfig` to find the name of your "
"wireless network interface. If it's `wlan0`, replace `SSID` and `passphrase` "
"with your data and run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:77
msgid ""
"# wpa_supplicant -B -i wlan0 -c <(wpa_passphrase 'SSID' 'passphrase') &\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:81
msgid ""
"Once you see in your terminal that connection is established, run `host "
"nixos.org` to check that the DNS resolves correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:83
msgid "In case you've made a typo, run `pkill wpa_supplicant` and start over."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:85
msgid "Updating firmware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:87
msgid ""
"To benefit from updates and bug fixes from the vendor, we'll start by "
"updating Raspberry Pi firmware:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:89
msgid ""
"# nix-shell -p raspberrypi-eeprom\n"
"# mount /dev/disk/by-label/FIRMWARE /mnt\n"
"# BOOTFS=/mnt FIRMWARE_RELEASE_STATUS=stable rpi-eeprom-update -d -a\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:95
msgid "Installing and configuring NixOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:97
msgid ""
"Now we'll install NixOS with our own configuration, here creating a `guest` "
"user and enabling the SSH daemon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:99
msgid ""
"In the `let` binding below, change the value of the `SSID` and "
"`SSIDpassword` variables to the `SSID` and `passphrase` values you used "
"previously:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:101
msgid ""
"{ config, pkgs, lib, ... }:\n"
"\n"
"let\n"
"  user = \"guest\";\n"
"  password = \"guest\";\n"
"  SSID = \"mywifi\";\n"
"  SSIDpassword = \"mypassword\";\n"
"  interface = \"wlan0\";\n"
"  hostname = \"myhostname\";\n"
"in {\n"
"\n"
"  boot = {\n"
"    kernelPackages = pkgs.linuxKernel.packages.linux_rpi4;\n"
"    initrd.availableKernelModules = [ \"xhci_pci\" \"usbhid\" "
"\"usb_storage\" ];\n"
"    loader = {\n"
"      grub.enable = false;\n"
"      generic-extlinux-compatible.enable = true;\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  fileSystems = {\n"
"    \"/\" = {\n"
"      device = \"/dev/disk/by-label/NIXOS_SD\";\n"
"      fsType = \"ext4\";\n"
"      options = [ \"noatime\" ];\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  networking = {\n"
"    hostName = hostname;\n"
"    wireless = {\n"
"      enable = true;\n"
"      networks.\"${SSID}\".psk = SSIDpassword;\n"
"      interfaces = [ interface ];\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  environment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [ vim ];\n"
"\n"
"  services.openssh.enable = true;\n"
"\n"
"  users = {\n"
"    mutableUsers = false;\n"
"    users.\"${user}\" = {\n"
"      isNormalUser = true;\n"
"      password = password;\n"
"      extraGroups = [ \"wheel\" ];\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  hardware.enableRedistributableFirmware = true;\n"
"  system.stateVersion = \"23.11\";\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:157
msgid "To save time on typing the whole configuration, download it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:159
msgid ""
"# curl -L https://tinyurl.com/tutorial-nixos-install-rpi4 > /etc/nixos/"
"configuration.nix\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:164
msgid ""
"Credentials you write into a NixOS configuration will be stored in plain "
"text in your `/nix/store` when that configuration is built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:166
msgid ""
"If you **don't** want this to happen, you can enter your credentials at a "
"console or use one of the community's solutions for encrypted secrets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:169
msgid ""
"Due to the way the `nixos-sd-image` is designed, NixOS is actually *already "
"installed* at this point, so we only need to `nixos-rebuild` with our new "
"configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:171
msgid ""
"# nixos-rebuild boot\n"
"# reboot\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:176
msgid ""
"If your system doesn't boot, select the oldest configuration in the "
"bootloader menu to get back to the live image and start over."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:178
msgid "Making changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:180
msgid "It booted, congratulations!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:182
msgid ""
"To make further changes to the configuration, [search through NixOS options]"
"(https://search.nixos.org/options), edit `/etc/nixos/configuration.nix`, and "
"update your system:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:185
msgid ""
"$ sudo -i\n"
"# nixos-rebuild switch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:190
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr "下一步"

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:192
msgid ""
"Once you have a working OS, try upgrading it with `nixos-rebuild switch --"
"upgrade` to install more recent package versions, and reboot to the old "
"configuration if something broke."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:193
msgid ""
"To enable hardware acceleration for a nice graphical desktop experience, add "
"the [`nixos-hardware`](https://github.com/nixos/nixos-hardware) module to "
"your configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:195
msgid ""
"imports = [\n"
"  \"${fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixos-hardware/tarball/"
"master\"}/raspberry-pi/4\"\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:201
msgid ""
"We recommend pinning the reference to `nixos-hardware`: [](ref-pinning-"
"nixpkgs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/installing-nixos-on-a-raspberry-pi.md:203
msgid ""
"To tweak bootloader options affecting hardware, [see `config.txt` options]"
"(https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/configuration/config-txt/). You "
"can change these options by running `mount /dev/disk/by-label/FIRMWARE /mnt` "
"and opening `/mnt/config.txt`."
msgstr ""
